dmca.title: Thesislife blog complains of copied work
dmca.body:
Per your instructions, sent to me via email at [private]@yahoo.com on February 3, 2006:

1.	Identify in sufficient detail the copyrighted work that you believe has been infringed upon. This must include identification of specific posts, as opposed to entire sites. Posts must be referenced by either the dates in which they appear or the permalink of the post.

The permalink of the post that contains my copyrighted work is
http://thesislife.blogspot.com/2006/01/helpfuI-links-for-pops-illustrations.html

2.	Identify the material that you claim is infringing upon the copyrighted work listed in item #1 above.

The specific item in this post that is my copyrighted artwork is this image: http://photos1.blogger.com/blogger/8115/1163/320/MonalisaCD.jpg

The creation of this piece of artwork by me is documented, step by step, on the page where the image was captured by your blog owner:
http://www.lisavollrath.com/pages/11

Please notice the very clear copyright notification on the bottom of this page:
